The paper focuses on feature extraction using neural networks and latent Dirichlet allocation for movie synopses. This falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain, which is covered by the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques for feature extraction and recommendation systems suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
